    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pointed tweezers for lifting knots from wool, so that their luster is not lost by handling them.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000018191/Diagram Group and Midgley, Handtools of Arts and Crafts (1981)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>拔除毛織品上小結的尖頭小鉗，避免在處理毛纖維時讓織品時失去光澤。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Puntige pincet om knopen uit de wol te halen, zodat de glans niet verloren gaat in het gebruik.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
